wiki/Epithelium\" rel=\"nofollow\">epithelium<\/a> sure you can.<\/p>\n\n<p>That's actually the way the <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Skin_allergy_test\" rel=\"nofollow\">skin allergy test<\/a> is all about: The physician tries a wide variety - <em>last time I did it were 28 well known kinds<\/em> - of substances in liquid form (drops). If an allergic reaction is caused, the physician takes note. Even very small quantities can cause allergic reactions. <\/p>\n\n<p>These tests are usually made in a secured environment (physician's office, hospital, etc) at a very low level which most of the times, if result is positive will cause just an irritation. The level of irritation will be self-explanatory, so even a non trained patient can understand what is going on.<\/p>\n\n<p>Not sure if <em>that<\/em> what you were asking though.<\/p>\n\n<p>Best Regards,<\/p>\n\n<p>pa<\/p>\n","answer_id":7202,"question_id":7200,"up_vote_count":4}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/7200/is-it-possible-to-give-a-person-an-allergic-reaction-in-a-very-specific-place","last_activity_date":1360849073,"creation_date":1360819521,"answer_count":1,"title":"Is it possible to give a person an allergic reaction in a very specific place?","body":"<p>Can I give a person an allergic reaction at a very specific spot in a tissue?\nAnd if so, how accurate can i get? <\/p>\n","question_id":7200,"tags":["human-biology","cell-biology","immunology"],"score":1,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":85,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1360849073},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/fd3877ba75ec0f883bdc21784f4124c7?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":3077,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3077/michael-pankov","reputation":106,"display_name":"Michael Pankov"},"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a03f4ba097a4c109e0895af070ac049c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","u