Olney's lesions never being directly observed in primates like humans, permanent brain damage from chronic ketamine exposure has been observed in adolescent cynomolgus monkeys.<sup>1<\/sup><\/p>\n\n<h2>Reference List<\/h2>\n\n<ol>\n<li>Sun, Lin; Qi Li, Qing Li, Yuzhe Zhang, Dexiang Liu, Hong Jiang, Fang Pan, David T. Yew (2012). \"<a href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/adb.12004/abstract\" rel=\"nofollow\">Chronic ketamine exposure induces permanent impairment of brain functions in adolescent cynomolgus monkeys<\/a>\". Addiction Biology. doi:<a href=\"http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/adb.12004/abstract\" rel=\"nofollow\">10.1111/adb.12004<\/a>. PMID <a href=\"http://www.ncbi.nlm.nih.gov/pubmed/23145560\" rel=\"nofollow\">23145560<\/a>. <\/li>\n<\/ol>\n","question_id":7179,"tags":["pharmacology","receptor","hallucinogens"],"score":1,"accepted_answer_id":7182,"down_vote_count":0,"is_answered":true,"view_count":328,"up_vote_count":1,"last_edit_date":1360646756},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/0syJT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1813,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1813/brenton-horne","reputation":1198,"display_name":"Brenton Horne","accept_rate":32},"answers":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/a03f4ba097a4c109e0895af070ac049c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":3032,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/3032/brian","reputation":379,"display_name":"Brian","accept_rate":100},"score":1,"is_accepted":false,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/0syJT.jpg?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1813,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1813/brenton-horne","reputation":1198,"display_name":"Brenton Horne","accept_rate":32},"score":0,"post_id":7164,"edited":false,"creation_date":1360560421,"comment_id":8794,"body":"Thanks, an answer is better than none at all. I&#39;m afraid I probably won&#39;t accep