ifferently, neural networks become trained, muscles change. Over many years these can be enormous. This is true of all humans, absent those with severe genetic faults.<\/p>\n\n<p>Genetics probably has a stronger influence on the psychological traits which might induce someone to train so hard. Though parenting could certainly override this.<\/p>\n","answer_id":5045,"question_id":3165,"up_vote_count":0},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":4,"is_accepted":true,"comments":[{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/RWd7T.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":658,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/658/719016","reputation":952,"display_name":"719016","accept_rate":56},"score":0,"post_id":5165,"edited":false,"creation_date":1352466042,"comment_id":7380,"body":"I am thinking that another good example could be &#39;sumo wrestlers&#39;, who are also very different in body types to the average population."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":0,"post_id":5165,"reply_to_user":{"profile_image":"https://i.stack.imgur.com/RWd7T.png?s=128&g=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":658,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/658/719016","reputation":952,"display_name":"719016","accept_rate":56},"edited":false,"creation_date":1352717357,"comment_id":7411,"body":"here is a paper which finds a candidate gene for physical athletic superiority (<a href=\"http://www.springerlink.com/content/hwllqyy12x29tpde/\" rel=\"nofollow\">springerlink.com/content/hwllqy