iology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":0,"post_id":7060,"edited":false,"creation_date":1360013397,"comment_id":8624,"body":"You can get the basic mechanistic details on wikipedia <a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ripening\" rel=\"nofollow\">en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Ripening<\/a> - for example fruits are shipped before ripe and then gassed with ethylene. This is a chemical important in apoptosis and ripening processes, it is given off by ripe/damaged fruits. So, what you can do is pick fruit before it is ripe, store it in a cool dark place then when you want to ripen put the desired amount in a paper bag with a few slices of apple."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/210cc4a4b2f281aaffe0b26521fe1ab8?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG&f=1","user_type":"registered","user_id":1590,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1590/rg255","reputation":11513,"display_name":"rg255","accept_rate":66},"score":1,"post_id":7060,"edited":false,"creation_date":1360013467,"comment_id":8625,"body":"@rsegal (can I recommend you change this question completely to ask &quot;what are the mechanisms which cause fruit to ripen?&quot; or something along those lines)"},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/66c66c4d97a7bc3859a85253f003e1fb?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"moderator","user_id":6,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/6/mad-scientist","reputation":6781,"display_name":"Mad Scientist","accept_rate":55},"score":0,"post_id":7060,"edited":false,"creation_date":1360068247,"comment_id":8636,"body":"I&#39;m closing this as <a href=\"http://cooking.stackexchange.com/questions/30703/how-do-banana-peels-reflect-its-ripening-state-can-we-influence-that-in-our-kit\">it has been answered on Seasoned Advice<\/a>"}],"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/questions/7060/what-are-the-mechanisms-that-cause-bananas-to-ripen-how-is-or-isnt-it-related","last_activity_date":13