is Could you clarify? The kidneys and bladder <i>are<\/i> located within the abdomen of quadrupeds (and us)."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/166093d036b7185b3a53052889d99e47?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1472,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1472/mew","reputation":836,"display_name":"Mew","accept_rate":86},"score":0,"post_id":5741,"edited":false,"creation_date":1358217264,"comment_id":8296,"body":"Yes I meant urinary duct, not system, which is located where the reproductive system is.  That is, why are these located in the same spot as each other.  Your second paragraph explained for the reproductive system, but not the urinary duct."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/06b0c88bb86cb532fc94663c6a566a0c?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":827,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/827/octern","reputation":418,"display_name":"octern"},"score":0,"post_id":5741,"edited":false,"creation_date":1358266400,"comment_id":8301,"body":"Nice job giving an answer that avoids the pitfalls of naive adaptationism. The presence of a trait doesn&#39;t mean it&#39;s a good idea, just that it&#39;s not bad enough to kill anyone (and/or kill their chances at reproducing)."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/41f11d6ee714fc25795c250b66fda568?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1899,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1899/joe-z","reputation":208,"display_name":"Joe Z."},"score":0,"post_id":5741,"edited":false,"creation_date":1359468104,"comment_id":8529,"body":"I was asking where it came from in the first place, not why it didn&#39;t change."},{"owner":{"profile_image":"https://www.gravatar.com/avatar/ef6c1e9a540c28587fe777f9bcf907af?s=128&d=identicon&r=PG","user_type":"registered","user_id":1231,"link":"http://biology.stackexchange.com/users/1231/mcm","reputation":7783,"display_name":"MCM"},"score":0,"post